## 🔍 Section 2: Agent Architecture Validation

### Is 4 Agents Over-Engineering?

**Research finding**: Amazon Bedrock allows a **maximum of 10 collaborator agents** per supervisor. Best practice is to "start small, clearly define, and scale."

**Analysis for NidhiAI (currently 4 agents)**:

| Agent | Role | Essential? | Verdict |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 🕵️ Grant Scout | Finds CSR opportunities from company reports | ✅ Yes — core value prop | **KEEP** |
| ⚖️ Compliance Officer | Checks NGO documents for legal compliance | ✅ Yes — unique differentiator | **KEEP** |
| 📝 Proposal Architect | Writes the grant proposal using RAG | ✅ Yes — the "output" | **KEEP** |
| 📊 Impact Dashboard | Auto-generates quarterly reports | ❌ Not for MVP | **REMOVE for hackathon** |

> [!TIP]
> **Optimization**: Reduce NidhiAI from 4 agents to **3 agents** for the hackathon MVP. This satisfies the "don't over-engineer" principle while still showcasing the Supervisor Pattern. The 3 agents have *clearly distinct roles* — this is exactly what AWS best practices recommend.

**Analysis for FreelanceForce (currently 4 agents)**:

| Agent | Role | Essential? | Verdict |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 🕵️ Gig Scout | Finds freelance gigs from web sources | ✅ Yes — core value prop | **KEEP** |
| 🧠 Strategy Supervisor | Analyzes match between student and gig | ⚠️ This IS the supervisor, not a separate agent | **MERGE into Supervisor** |
| ✍️ Pitch Architect | Writes personalized proposals | ✅ Yes — the "output" | **KEEP** |
| 💰 Rate Negotiator | Advises on pricing | ❌ Nice-to-have, not essential for MVP | **REMOVE for hackathon** |

> **Optimization**: Reduce FreelanceForce from 4 to **2 specialist agents + 1 supervisor**. Supervisor handles strategy. Scout finds gigs. Writer drafts proposals. Clean.

